code:
```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.set_title('What is the trend of wheat production over the years?', wrap=True)
    chart.set_xlabel('Year')
    chart.set_ylabel('Wheat Production')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wheat', color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['wheat'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['wheat'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wheat production?')
    plt.xlabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.strftime('%Y')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='year', y='wages', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['wages'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Average Wage: {data['wages'].mean():.2f}")
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)
plt.title('What is the average wage per year?', wrap=True)
plt.show()
```

```
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['wheat', 'wages']]
    corr = data.corr()
    sns.heatmap(corr, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between wheat production and wages?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
